<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?>
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             x:Class="SpreadsheetGUI.HelpPage"
             Title="Spreadsheet Help">
    <VerticalStackLayout>
        <Label 
            Text="How to use this spreadsheet:"
            
            VerticalOptions="StartAndExpand" 
            HorizontalOptions="StartAndExpand"
            FontSize="Title"/>
        <Label
            Text="1.Select a cell. You can click on individual cell"
            VerticalOptions="StartAndExpand" 
            HorizontalOptions="StartAndExpand"
            FontSize="Large"
            Padding="10"/>
        <Label
            Text="2. You will see the cell name, value box, and contents box. Enter the preferred contents of the cell(formula, letters, words, numbers)."
            VerticalOptions="StartAndExpand" 
            HorizontalOptions="StartAndExpand"
            Padding="10"
            FontSize="Large"/>

        <Label
            Text=" 3. Notice the value of the cell updates according to the contents, which is stays the same exactly how it was entered. "
            VerticalOptions="StartAndExpand" 
            HorizontalOptions="StartAndExpand"
            Padding="10"
            FontSize="Large"/>
        <Label
            Text="4. Notice the Set button. If you click on set, you can manually set the value and contents without pressing enter/return."
            VerticalOptions="StartAndExpand" 
            HorizontalOptions="StartAndExpand"
            Padding="10"
            FontSize="Large"/>
        <Label
            Text="5. Notice the Sum column/row buttons. If you click Sum selected row or column, the sum of that row or column will be set as the contents of the selected cell."
            VerticalOptions="StartAndExpand" 
            HorizontalOptions="StartAndExpand"
            Padding="10"
            FontSize="Large"/>
        <Label
            Text="6. Notice the menu bar on the top left. If you select file, a dropdown menu appears. Select New to open a new empty spreadsheet that replaces the current displayed spreadsheet. Select open to open a .sprd file in the system directory to a spreadsheet in the GUI. Select Save to write the current displayed spreadsheet to a .sprd file in the system directory documents folder. Selecting close will quit the application.  "
            VerticalOptions="StartAndExpand" 
            HorizontalOptions="StartAndExpand"
            Padding="10"
            FontSize="Large"/>
         </VerticalStackLayout>
</ContentPage>
